# Notes & To-Do — Unity Editor Window

A lightweight, single-script editor tool that adds a notes and to-do list window to Unity. No packages, no assets in your build — just a simple editor extension stored entirely in `EditorPrefs`.

---

## Features

- **Categories** — Create, rename, reorder, and delete groups to organize your work.
- **To-Do Items** — Add checkbox items to any category. Mark them complete, edit inline, or delete.
- **Notes** — Each category has a freeform text area for general notes.
- **Toolbar** — Collapse/expand all categories and bulk-clear completed items.
- **Zero Project Footprint** — Data is stored in `EditorPrefs` (your machine's registry/plist). Nothing is added to your project's assets, scenes, or builds.

---

## Requirements

- **Unity 6+** (tested on 6000.3.11f1 LTS). Should work on older versions as well — the APIs used are long-standing.

---

## Installation

1. In your Unity project's `Assets` folder, create a folder called `Editor` if one doesn't already exist:

   ```
   Assets/
   └── Editor/
   ```

2. Copy **`NotesEditorWindow.cs`** into that `Editor` folder:

   ```
   Assets/
   └── Editor/
       └── NotesEditorWindow.cs
   ```

   > **Why an `Editor` folder?** Unity treats any folder named `Editor` as editor-only. Scripts inside are compiled into a separate assembly that is stripped from builds automatically. This means the tool will never end up in your game.

3. Wait for Unity to recompile (you'll see the progress bar at the bottom of the editor).

4. Open the window via the menu bar:

   ```
   Window → General → Notes and To-Do
   ```

5. Dock it wherever you like — next to the Inspector, Console, or as a floating window.

---

## Usage

### Creating a Category

Type a name in the **"New Category"** field at the bottom of the window and click **Add Category**.

### Adding a To-Do Item

Inside any category, type your task in the text field and click the **+** button.

### Completing / Editing Items

- Click the **checkbox** to mark an item as complete. Completed items are greyed out.
- Click the **text** of any item to edit it inline.
- Click **✕** to delete a single item.

### Notes

Each category has a **Notes** text area at the bottom of its section. Use it for freeform text — context, links, reminders, etc.

### Toolbar Actions

| Button              | Action                                               |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| **Collapse All**    | Folds every category closed.                         |
| **Expand All**      | Opens every category.                                |
| **Clear Completed** | Removes all completed items across every category.   |

### Reordering Categories

Use the **▲** and **▼** buttons on each category header to move it up or down.

---

## Data Storage

All data is stored in **`EditorPrefs`** under the key `EditorTools_NotesData`.

**What this means:**

- Notes persist between Unity sessions on the **same machine**.
- Notes are **not** shared via version control or across machines.
- Notes are **not** included in builds.
- Uninstalling the script does not automatically delete saved data. To clear it manually, use `EditorPrefs.DeleteKey("EditorTools_NotesData")` in a console or script.

---

## Uninstalling

1. Delete `Assets/Editor/NotesEditorWindow.cs` from your project.
2. *(Optional)* Clear stored data by running this in a Unity editor script or the Immediate window:
   ```csharp
   EditorPrefs.DeleteKey("EditorTools_NotesData");
   ```

